Class JiaoDrone

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mmkrusniak.drone.Drone
      • com.mmkrusniak.drone.static_height.OfflineDrone
        • com.mmkrusniak.drone.static_height.JiaoDrone
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CombinatoryJiaoDrone
    public class JiaoDrone
extends OfflineDrone
    An offline drone which splits complex polygons into simpler ones by splitting concave vertices using a minimalized version of Jiao's cellular decomposition. It performs well but the decomposition is very time-intensive.

      • decompose

        public java.util.List<Polygon> decompose​(Polygon polygon,
                                         int depth)
        Splits a complex region into more easily traversible subregions. It is a recursive algorithm.
        Parameters:
        polygon - A polygon to decompose.
        depth - The maximum depth to which to recurse. Decomposition also will stop before this when all subregions are acceptable.
        Returns:
        A list of polygons which are easily traversed and whose union forms the original polygon.

      • isAcceptable

        protected boolean isAcceptable​(Polygon p)
        Gives the end condition for the decomposition. For Huang's algorithm, the polygon must only be simply traversable (not necessarily concave).
        Parameters:
        p - A polygon.
        Returns:
        Whether the algorithm needs to decompose that polygon.
